[2] Global update (Pakistan, DR Congo, Ghana, Philippines) - GPEI/WHO
Date: Thu 3 Oct 2019
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative/WHO [edited]
http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus weekly update: 2 Oct 2019, WHO
---------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus cases isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 3
Environment: 13

Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2019: [85]
Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2018: 33

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 3
Environment: 11
Others: 2

Total number of cVDPV cases (all types) in 2019: [88]
Total number of cVDPV cases (all types) in 2018: 104

Headlines
Summary of new viruses (AFP cases and positive environmental samples) this week:
- Pakistan - 3 WPV1 cases and 13 WPV1-positive environmental samples;
- Democratic Republic of the Congo - 1 circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) case;
- Ghana - 1 cVDPV2 case and 5 positive environmental samples;
- Philippines - 1 cVDPV2 case, 1 cVDPV2 and 5 cVDPV1 positive environmental samples.

Afghanistan
- No wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) case was reported. There are 16 WPV1 cases reported in 2019. There were 21 WPV1 cases reported in 2018.

Pakistan
- 3 WPV1 cases were reported: 2 from Bannu and Lakki Marwat districts in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province and 1 from Jamshoro district, Sindh province. The onsets of paralysis were on [19, 26 and 23 Aug 2019], respectively. As of this week, a total of 69 WPV1 cases have been reported in 2019. Full year total of WPV1 cases for year 2018 is 12.
- 13 WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported: 1 each from the districts of Dadu, Karachi Orangi, Hyderabad, Karachi Baldia and Karachi Saddar and 2 each in Sukkur and Karachi Gadap districts, Sindh province. One sample was also reported in Quetta district, Balochistan province, 1 in DG Khan and 2 in Lahore, Punjab Province. The samples were collected between [11 and 18 Sep 2019].

Nigeria
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There are 16 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2019. There were 34 cVDPV2 cases in 2018.

Lake Chad
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week.
- In the Lake Chad region, cVDPV2 linked to the outbreak originating in Nigeria has been detected in Niger (1 case in 2019 and 10 cases in 2018) and in Cameroon (1 positive environmental sample, collected on [20 Apr 2019] in Extreme Nord).
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across the Lake Chad subregion remains high.

Benin
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There is one cVDPV2 case in 2019 linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.

Ghana
- 1 case of cVDPV2 was reported this week from Saboba district, Northern province. The onset of paralysis was on [9 Sep 2019]. There are 2 cVDPV2 cases in 2019 linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.
- 5 cVDPV2 positive environmental surveillance samples were collected -- 3 in Accra Metropolis district in the Greater Accra province and 2 in Northern Sub Metro, Northern Tamale province. The samples were collected between [28 Aug 2019] and [10 Sep 2019].
- Surveillance is being strengthened in neighbouring Togo, Cote d'Ivoire and Burkina Faso.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.

Democratic Republic of the Congo
- 1 case of cVDPV2 was reported this week from Mukanga district, Haut Lomami province. The onset of paralysis was on [20 Aug 2019]. There are 31 cVDPV2 cases in 2019 and 20 in 2018.

Angola
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There [are] a total of 18 cVDPV2 cases from 6 outbreaks reported in 2019.

Central African Republic (CAR)
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There are 6 reported cases in 2019 from 5 different outbreaks of cVDPV2 in 2019. Additional confirmed cVDPV2 community contact have been reported in CAR.
- No cVDPV2-positive environmental sample was reported.

Horn of Africa
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There are 2 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2019.
- Somalia has reported a total of 15 cVDPV cases (8 type 2, 6 type 3 and 1 coinfection of both type 2 and type 3) since the beginning of the outbreaks. The most recent cVDPV3 virus was from an AFP case from Runingod district, Middle Shabelle province with an onset date of paralysis on [7 Sep 2018]. cVDPV2 has also been detected during 2018 in one environmental sample in Kenya collected on [21 Mar 2018]. There are also 2 reported cases of cVDPV2 in Ethiopia, linked to Somalia in 2019.

Papua New Guinea
- No new cases of cVDPV1 were reported this week. There were 26 cases reported in 2018.

Mozambique
- No case of cVDPV2 was been reported this week. There was one case reported in 2018.

Indonesia
- No cVDPV1 cases were reported this week. One cVDPV1 case was reported in 2018 from Papua province with onset of paralysis on [28 Nov 2018].
- This outbreak is not linked to the cVDPV1 in neighbouring Papua New Guinea.

Iran
- No new WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported this week. In total, 3 WPV1-positive environmental samples have been reported in 2019, all from Sistan and Balochistan province. The isolated viruses have been detected in environmental samples only, and genetic sequencing confirms they are linked to WPV1 circulating in Karachi, Pakistan.

China
- No cVDPV2 cases were reported this week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases in the country remains one.

Myanmar
- No cVDPV1 cases were reported this week. There are 6 reported cases of cVDPV1 in 2019.

Philippines
- 1 case of cVPDV2 was reported this week from the province of Lanao Del Sur, Mindanao. The onset of paralysis was on [26 Jun 2019].
- 5 positive cVDPV1 and 1 cVDPV2 environmental samples were reported from Manila district in the National Capital Region. They were collected between [1 Jul 2019 and 29 Aug 2019].

