[While the above report appears quite lengthy, it is a very comprehensive analysis of the current situation with polio with concrete recommendations on how to proceed going forward. The issues touched on are issues that have not really changed from prior reports, aside from the increasing geographic extent of problems with cVDPVs this year (2019).

A question that should be addressed is whether it is time to make the full switch to IPV and eliminate OPV. It is also curious that with all of the vaccine refusal incidents in Pakistan and Afghanistan there have been no reports of cVDPVs in either country through the years.... - Mod.MPP]
